Performs gene-set analysis with MAGMA, using gwf.


Requirements:

Python pandas

MAGMA: http://ctg.cncr.nl/software/magma

gwf: http://mailund.github.io/gwf/

The association studies from which the gene p values are derived, in the format expected by MAGMA.


usage: run.py [-h] [--gwf GWF] [--snploc SNPLOC] [--studyfolder STUDYFOLDER]
              [--geneloc GENELOC] [--setfile SETFILE] [--folder FOLDER]

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --gwf GWF             the path to the gwf workflow
  --snploc SNPLOC       plink file stub, such as hapmap or 1000 genomes (see
                        MAGMA documentation)
  --studyfolder STUDYFOLDER
                        the folder containing the studies with the snp p
                        values
  --geneloc GENELOC     gene locations file (see MAGMA documentation)
  --setfile SETFILE     gene set file (see MAGMA documentation)
  --folder FOLDER       folder where output files are placed

